Summary (concise)

Findings
- Root cause: two contributing failures — (1) orchestrator worker frequently reported "no_queued_task" while planner created tasks (so scheduled learning runs weren't executed), and (2) earlier bug in SimulationExecutionEngine (stale quote parsing / freshness guard) prevented trade closures → no new review reports → learning starved.
- Evidence: planner/worker logs, DB snapshot, previous lifecycle fix, and manual run.

Actions & verification
- Ran autonomous learning against local dev DB (env DATABASE_URL=file:/.../prisma/dev.db) — a fresh StrategyLearningInsight was generated: id=109 (generatedAt=2026-04-27T02:00:17Z), sourceCount=50.
- Created diagnosis report at docs/reports/learning_pipeline_health.md and committed it.

Forbidden actions
- None performed (no fake insights, no threshold changes, no live broker access).

Artifacts
- docs/reports/learning_pipeline_health.md
- New DB row: StrategyLearningInsight id=109

Recommended next steps
- Investigate why worker saw `no_queued_task` despite planner-created tasks (orchestrator task queue visibility / permissions).
- Re-enable/monitor scheduled planner+worker for 3 days to confirm automated regeneration.
- Monitor TradeReviewReport creation and learning sourceCount.

Handoff answers
- Acceptance criteria: root cause identified and documented; pipeline verified end-to-end; new insight generated (id=109); report written.
- Forbidden actions: not performed.
- Artifacts produced: report + DB evidence (insight id 109).

